<subSubSection id="5B92BEDEFFC6DD01CEBCF7C8F883F41A" pageId="2" pageNumber="840" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="1337ED55FFC6DD01CEBCF7C8F883F41A" blockId="2.[1981,2574,2062,2485]" lastBlockId="2.[1369,2575,2491,3233]" pageId="2" pageNumber="840">
Placed in the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="D48896D6FFC6DD01C00CF7C8F6F5F7BD" box="[2319,2429,2141,2170]" class="Mammalia" family="Gliridae" genus="Claviglis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="2" pageNumber="840" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Claviglis</taxonomicName>
. Based on external appearance, this species is somewhat similar to 
<taxonomicName id="D48896D6FFC6DD01C1A1F725F604F70E" authorityName="Holden &amp; Levine" authorityYear="2009" box="[2210,2444,2224,2249]" class="Mammalia" family="Gliridae" genus="Graphiurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="2" pageNumber="840" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="walterverheyeni">G. walterverheyeni</taxonomicName>
, but it is much larger in body size and differs in cranial proportions. In 1969, D. R. Rosevear and M. E. Holden in 1996 hypothesized that morphological similarity between 
<taxonomicName id="D48896D6FFC6DD01CEC2F6E4F717F649" baseAuthorityName="Jentink" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[1985,2207,2417,2446]" class="Mammalia" family="Gliridae" genus="Graphiurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="2" pageNumber="876" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="crassicaudatus">G. crassicaudatus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="D48896D6FFC6DD01C1E4F6E4F601F649" box="[2279,2441,2417,2446]" class="Mammalia" family="Gliridae" genus="Graphiurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="2" pageNumber="840" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nagtglasu">G. nagtglasu</taxonomicName>
reflected a close phylogenetic relationship between the two species. A cladistic analysis of African dormice based on cranial and middle ear characters by I. Y. Pavlinov &amp; E. G. Potapova in 2003, however, does not support this contention; their study showed that the characters shared by 
<taxonomicName id="D48896D6FFC6DD01C1F2F587F658F5EC" baseAuthorityName="Jentink" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[2289,2512,2578,2603]" class="Mammalia" family="Gliridae" genus="Graphiurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="2" pageNumber="876" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="crassicaudatus">G. crassicaudatus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="D48896D6FFC6DD01CC5EF5A3F98AF594" authorityName="Jentink" authorityYear="1888" box="[1373,1538,2614,2643]" class="Mammalia" family="Gliridae" genus="Graphiurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="2" pageNumber="840" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nagtglasii">G. nagtglasii</taxonomicName>
may be primitive for the genus and that 
<taxonomicName id="D48896D6FFC6DD01C15FF5A3F6B6F594" baseAuthorityName="Jentink" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[2140,2366,2614,2643]" class="Mammalia" family="Gliridae" genus="Graphiurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="2" pageNumber="840" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="crassicaudatus">G. crassicaudatus</taxonomicName>
shares certain derived characters with other species of 
<taxonomicName id="D48896D6FFC6DD01CE9BF5C8F7A3F5BD" authorityName="Smuts" authorityYear="1832" box="[1944,2091,2653,2682]" class="Mammalia" family="Gliridae" genus="Graphiurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="2" pageNumber="840" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Graphiurus</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="D48896D6FFC6DD01C13CF5C8F614F5BD" authorityName="Holden &amp; Levine" authorityYear="2009" box="[2111,2460,2653,2682]" class="Mammalia" family="Gliridae" genus="Graphiurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="2" pageNumber="840" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="walterverheyeni">Graphiurus walterverheyeni</taxonomicName>
was not yet described when Pavlinov and Potapova’s analysis was performed; based on cranial traits, Holden and R. S. Levine in 2009 postulated a close relationship between 
<taxonomicName id="D48896D6FFC6DD01C0B3F532FA6BF528" baseAuthorityName="Jentink" baseAuthorityYear="1888" class="Mammalia" family="Gliridae" genus="Graphiurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="2" pageNumber="840" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="crassicaudatus">G. crassicaudatus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="D48896D6FFC6DD01CF3AF55BF8AEF528" authorityName="Holden &amp; Levine" authorityYear="2009" box="[1593,1830,2766,2799]" class="Mammalia" family="Gliridae" genus="Graphiurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="2" pageNumber="867" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="walterverheyeni">G. walterverheyeni</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="D48896D6FFC6DD01CE3CF55BF713F528" baseAuthorityName="Jentink" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[1855,2203,2766,2799]" class="Mammalia" family="Gliridae" genus="Graphiurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="2" pageNumber="840" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="crassicaudatus">Graphiurus crassicaudatus</taxonomicName>
have not been recorded from DR Congo; in 2008, P. Grubb and D. A. Schlitter noted an unidentified example of 
<taxonomicName id="D48896D6FFC6DD01CC85F4B7F991F4F8" authorityName="Smuts" authorityYear="1832" box="[1414,1561,2850,2879]" class="Mammalia" family="Gliridae" genus="Graphiurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="2" pageNumber="840" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Graphiurus</taxonomicName>
in the British Museum from southern DR Congo that was previously thought to represent 
<taxonomicName id="D48896D6FFC6DD01CF89F4D0F8E1F4A1" baseAuthorityName="Jentink" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[1674,1897,2885,2918]" class="Mammalia" family="Gliridae" genus="Graphiurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="2" pageNumber="876" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="crassicaudatus">G. crassicaudatus</taxonomicName>
, the specimen they referred tois likely the same specimen described later by Holden and Levine in 2009 as the holotype of 
<taxonomicName id="D48896D6FFC6DD01C06CF4E5FA21F473" authorityName="Holden &amp; Levine" authorityYear="2009" class="Mammalia" family="Gliridae" genus="Graphiurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="2" pageNumber="867" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="walterverheyeni">G. walterverheyeni</taxonomicName>
. In 2009, Holden and Levine discussed the validity of the record of 
<taxonomicName id="D48896D6FFC6DD01C06EF406FA29F41A" baseAuthorityName="Jentink" baseAuthorityYear="1888" class="Mammalia" family="Gliridae" genus="Graphiurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="2" pageNumber="876" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="crassicaudatus">G. crassicaudatus</taxonomicName>
from Bioko I. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5B92BEDEFFC6DD01CC59F47EF970F3EC" pageId="2" pageNumber="840" type="distribution">
<caption id="47F7BDDDFFC6DD01CC59F47EF970F3EC" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6604347" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6604347" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6604347/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="840" targetBox="[1367,1958,2071,2485]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph id="1337ED55FFC6DD01CC59F47EF970F3EC" blockId="2.[1369,2575,2491,3233]" pageId="2" pageNumber="840">
<emphasis id="21FC3147FFC6DD01CC59F47EF982F3C3" bold="true" box="[1370,1546,3051,3076]" pageId="2" pageNumber="840">Distribution.</emphasis>
W &amp; C Africa, from Liberia and SW Guinea E to SW Cameroon and Bioko I, but excluding Benin.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5B92BEDEFFC6DD00CC59F3A0FD4FFC07" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="841" pageId="2" pageNumber="840" type="description">
<paragraph id="1337ED55FFC6DD00CC59F3A0FD4FFC07" blockId="2.[1369,2575,2491,3233]" lastBlockId="3.[205,1414,305,2499]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="841" pageId="2" pageNumber="840">
<emphasis id="21FC3147FFC6DD01CC59F3A0F9DFF395" bold="true" box="[1370,1623,3125,3154]" pageId="2" pageNumber="840">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 83-98 mm, tail 55-70 mm, ear 11-14 mm, hindfoot 16-19 mm; weight 20-29 g. No information regarding sexual dimorphism has been reported. Dorsal pelage of the Thick-tailed African Dormouse is rufous brown or copper. Fur is soft and short, rump hairs are 4-5 mm, and guard hairs are up to 10 mm. Ventral pelage is gray washed with ocher, cream, or white, and dorsal and ventral pelage colors are clearly delineated. Eyes are large, and eye mask is conspicuous in some individuals, although others have only narrow dark eye-rings. Cheeks are paler than dorsal pelage. Ears are brown, short, and rounded, and post-auricular patches are usually not present. Hindfeet are solid white or white with dark metatarsal streak. The Thicktailed African Dormouse has one oftherelatively shortesttails in the genus, ¢.65%of head-body length. Tail hairs are shorter at base, 3-4 mm, with longer hairs toward tip, up to 27 mm. Tail ofthe type specimen was shed during injury, an exampleofthefalse tail autotomy exhibited by most species of 
<taxonomicName id="D48896D6FFC7DD00CA1CFD1AFC1AFD6B" authorityName="Muirhead" authorityYear="1819" box="[799,914,655,684]" class="Mammalia" family="Gliridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="3" pageNumber="841" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">Gliridae</taxonomicName>
. Dense, bushy regrowth oftail hairs makestail appear thicker than normal; tail has been described as “club-shaped,” hence the scientific name. Color ofdorsal and ventral surfaces oftail generally matches that of dorsum and does not exhibit white tip. Greatest length ofskull is 26-7-29-7 mm, zygomatic breadth is 13-3-16-7 mm, and upper tooth row length is 3-3-3 mm. Chromosome number is not known. Females usually have four pairs of nipples (I pectoral + I abdominal + 2 inguinal = 8), a female with only two pairs (0 pectoral + 0 abdominal + 2 inguinal = 4) has been reported.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="47F7BDDDFFC6DD01C963F296FC20F249" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6604445" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6604445" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6604445/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="840" startId="2.[96,126,3331,3352]" targetBox="[138,2681,125,3531]" targetPageId="1">
<paragraph id="1337ED55FFC6DD01C963F296FC20F249" blockId="2.[95,2541,3331,3473]" pageId="2" pageNumber="840">
On following pages: 3. Walter Verheyen’s African Dormouse (
<taxonomicName id="D48896D6FFC6DD01CBFEF296FBA2F2DF" authorityName="Holden &amp; Levine" authorityYear="2009" box="[765,1066,3331,3352]" class="Mammalia" family="Gliridae" genus="Graphiurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="2" pageNumber="840" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="walterverheyeni">Graphiurus walterverheyeni</taxonomicName>
); 4. Angolan African Dormouse (
<taxonomicName id="D48896D6FFC6DD01CC92F296F90BF2DF" authorityName="de Winton" authorityYear="1897" box="[1425,1667,3331,3352]" class="Mammalia" family="Gliridae" genus="Graphiurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="2" pageNumber="840" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="angolensis">Graphiurus angolensis</taxonomicName>
); 5. Christy's African Dormouse (
